{"raw_input_snapshot": {"task_id": "task-e9efb51ce7", "task_type": "TEXT_SUMMARIZATION", "task_parameters": {"text": "LOKESH VETTATH  \n8074173230 | lokeshvettath@gmail.com |  linkedin.com/in/lokesh-vettath  \ngithub.com/Lokesh983 | Madanapalle, Andhra Pradesh. \nPROFESSIONAL SUM MARY  \nI build clean, usable web interfaces with a strong focus on interaction, clarity, and product flow. I build frontend-heavy, multi-\nuser web applications using React, integrating REST APIs and backend logic where required. I care about building real \nproducts, iterating on feedback, and improving usability rather than adding unnecessary complexity.  \nSKILLS  \nFrontend: HTML, CSS, TailwindCSS, React \nBackend: Node.js, Express.js \nProgramming Languages: Python JavaScript \nUI/UX: Figma, Canva \nAPIs & API Tools: RESTful APIs, Postman \nDatabase: MongoDB, SQL \nVersion control: Git, GitHub \nDevelopment environments: WebStorm, Visual Studio Code \nPROJECTS  \n1. Microblogging Platform - React | JavaScript | REST APIs | UI/UX Design | Figma \nBuilt a multi -user web application that allows users to create posts, view a shared feed, and interact with content in a \nclean, responsive interface. The frontend was developed in React with a focus on component structure, state management, \nand smooth user  interactions. Integrated REST -based backend APIs to handle user actions and data persistence, \nprioritizing usability, clear product flow, and real-world behavior over unnecessary features. \n2. Interview Preparation Chatbot - React | JavaScript | REST APIs | UI/UX Design | Figma \nDeveloped an interactive web interface that allows users to practice interview questions and receive responses through a \nclean, distraction-free experience. Designed user flows and screen layouts in Figma before implementing them in React, \nfocusing on clarity, readability, and smooth interaction. Integrated the frontend with API -based backend logic to support \ndynamic content, keeping the emphasis on usability and product flow rather than visual or technical complexity.  \n3. Gesture-Controlled Virtual Interaction System – Python, OpenCV, MediaPipe, PyAutoGUI, PyCaw \nBuilt a gesture-based interaction system that enables hands -free control of basic OS functions such as mouse movement \nand volume adjustment using real -time hand tracking. Utilized OpenCV and MediaPipe for reliable landmark detection \nfrom webcam input, and integrated PyAutoGUI and PyCaw for system-level control. Focused on intuitive interaction cues \nand responsiveness to make the user experience clear and practical rather than complex.  \nEDUCATION  \nBachelor of Technology in Computer Science of Engineering, Specialized in Artificial Intelligence  \nAditya College of Engineering Madanapalle. | 2022-2026 | CGPA: 8.0 \nACHIEVEMENTS  \n• Founded the VOLAR student community to create a space focused on hands -on development, \ncollaboration, and peer learning.   \n• Planned and executed a college -level hackathon under VOLAR, coordinating teams, timelines, and \nexecution to deliver a high-impact problem-solving event"}, "task_source_id": "runner-demo", "task_schema_version": "1.0.0"}, "guardrail_decision": {"approved": true, "required_confirmation": false}, "executor_result": "Action executed successfully", "external_timestamp": "2026-03-20T00:00:00Z"}
